    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>The minimum value for a double is <code>Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> that's why <code>Double.MIN_VALUE</code> isn't really the minimum for a <code>Double</code>.</p>\n\n<p>As the double are floating point numbers, you can only have the biggest number (with a lower precision) or the closest number to 0 (with a great precision).</p>\n\n<p>If you really want a minimal value for a double that isn't infinity then you can use <code>-Double.MAX_VALUE</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 65509,
        "reputation" : 6313,
        "user_id" : 192720,
        "user_type" : "registered",
