      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@Sahuagin, it&#39;s not really &quot;supposed&quot; to be named anything particular. Epsilon is just a greek letter that commonly represents an arbitrarily small positive quantity in maths / physics. Go chose <code>SmallestNonzeroFloat64</code> for instance."
